# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: UnionKingdom | Scene: UnionKingdom12SupportAnother
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The room was spinning out of control."
    new "The room was spinning out of control."

    old "Edmond smashed his fist on the table."
    new "Edmond smashed his fist on the table."

    old "We have need of a strong leader! And you propose in a time of war we put a politician or a merchant in charge? Absurd!"
    new "We have need of a strong leader! And you propose in a time of war we put a politician or a merchant in charge? Absurd!"

    old "Gods, best we put Edmond in charge before he decides to kill us in the dead of night like he did with those children."
    new "Gods, best we put Edmond in charge before he decides to kill us in the dead of night like he did with those children."

    old "I will not have my honour questioned by some a man who would sell his wife for a sack of gold!"
    new "I will not have my honour questioned by some a man who would sell his wife for a sack of gold!"

    old "Please, gentlemen, you should not-"
    new "Please, gentlemen, you should not-"

    old "Sarah slammed the palms of her hands on the table and asserted herself."
    new "Sarah slammed the palms of her hands on the table and asserted herself."

    old "The room was quiet."
    new "The room was quiet."

    old "Rare to yell, when she did, it seemed to make an impression."
    new "Rare to yell, when she did, it seemed to make an impression."

    old "Divided like this, the Mythrans will eat us alive."
    new "Divided like this, the Mythrans will eat us alive."

    old "They'll come for us, one by one. Turning one against the other."
    new "They'll come for us, one by one. Turning one against the other."

    old "And when the dust settles, all these accusations will mean nothing, for the only banner that will wave over our houses is theirs."
    new "And when the dust settles, all these accusations will mean nothing, for the only banner that will wave over our houses is theirs."

    old "For once in your damned lives, put the interests of the people before your own."
    new "For once in your damned lives, put the interests of the people before your own."

    old "All of them stared at her. The room was quiet."
    new "All of them stared at her. The room was quiet."

    old "Say Statement"
    new "Say Statement"

    old "Support Maeiv"
    new "Support Maeiv"

    old "I pledge my support to Maeiv."
    new "I pledge my support to Maeiv."

    old "Sarah could see a smile come over Maeiv's face."
    new "Sarah could see a smile come over Maeiv's face."

    old "A most wise decision, my dear."
    new "A most wise decision, my dear."

    old "She was the one who saw this threat. Who gathered us all. Forged us into one."
    new "She was the one who saw this threat. Who gathered us all. Forged us into one."

    old "The path ahead will be one of war, yes, but it will bring about far more conflicts than just the clashing of steel."
    new "The path ahead will be one of war, yes, but it will bring about far more conflicts than just the clashing of steel."

    old "We will need a leader who can unite us, who understands the enemy and who can play the game better than anyone."
    new "We will need a leader who can unite us, who understands the enemy and who can play the game better than anyone."

    old "Maeiv bowed her head."
    new "Maeiv bowed her head."

    old "Well said, Sarah."
    new "Well said, Sarah."

    old "Together, the two women looked about the room."
    new "Together, the two women looked about the room."

    old "The men for their part quickly realized they had lost."
    new "The men for their part quickly realized they had lost."

    old "Antonio knew he had no support. Edmond would never give him any."
    new "Antonio knew he had no support. Edmond would never give him any."

    old "Edmond would rather have slit his own throat than beg the Duke for support."
    new "Edmond would rather have slit his own throat than beg the Duke for support."

    old "A wise choice indeed. One I can certainly live with."
    new "A wise choice indeed. One I can certainly live with."

    old "Maeiv gracefully bowed her head again."
    new "Maeiv gracefully bowed her head again."

    old "It is important that we are unified. For that, I will throw in my vote as well."
    new "It is important that we are unified. For that, I will throw in my vote as well."

    old "Maeiv had not needed it, but she acted as graceful as if she had."
    new "Maeiv had not needed it, but she acted as graceful as if she had."

    old "Whatever was to be said of the Silent Queen, we was not a poor winner."
    new "Whatever was to be said of the Silent Queen, we was not a poor winner."

    old "I vow to you all today that the power you grant me is not one that I take lightly."
    new "I vow to you all today that the power you grant me is not one that I take lightly."

    old "Rather, I would even almost call it a burden."
    new "Rather, I would even almost call it a burden."

    old "Antonio scoffed at Maeiv's exaggeration, but bit his tongue after."
    new "Antonio scoffed at Maeiv's exaggeration, but bit his tongue after."

    old "These extreme times call for extreme measures, and so with a heavy heart I will take on myself the title of old."
    new "These extreme times call for extreme measures, and so with a heavy heart I will take on myself the title of old."

    old "I will be the High Queen of the Union."
    new "I will be the High Queen of the Union."

    old "Sarah was the first to begin clapping, then the others joined."
    new "Sarah was the first to begin clapping, then the others joined."

    old "Her vote had carried the day and made Maeiv High Queen."
    new "Her vote had carried the day and made Maeiv High Queen."

    old "Support Edmond"
    new "Support Edmond"

    old "I pledge my support to Edmond."
    new "I pledge my support to Edmond."

    old "Edmond raised his hand, acknowledging her support."
    new "Edmond raised his hand, acknowledging her support."

    old "A wise choice, Sarah."
    new "A wise choice, Sarah."

    old "I always knew we saw the world the same way."
    new "I always knew we saw the world the same way."

    old "Antonio tried to protest."
    new "Antonio tried to protest."

    old "You expect me to live under this man? Who so constantly insults me?"
    new "You expect me to live under this man? Who so constantly insults me?"

    old "You are a very insultable man, Antonio. Be glad that is all I do."
    new "You are a very insultable man, Antonio. Be glad that is all I do."

    old "See? And now he threatens me too!"
    new "See? And now he threatens me too!"

    old "Be quiet."
    new "Be quiet."

    old "Be quiet you fat slob!"
    new "Be quiet you fat slob!"

    old "The room went quiet."
    new "The room went quiet."

    old "Sarah saw Maeiv's eyes moving from side to side."
    new "Sarah saw Maeiv's eyes moving from side to side."

    old "In only a moment, she had made her calculation."
    new "In only a moment, she had made her calculation."

    old "She had only her own support. Edmond held two votes. Antonio was not the kind of man she wanted to be begging for support."
    new "She had only her own support. Edmond held two votes. Antonio was not the kind of man she wanted to be begging for support."

    old "And even if she did, she would only have two votes against two. The two weakest militaries, opposite the two strongest."
    new "And even if she did, she would only have two votes against two. The two weakest militaries, opposite the two strongest."

    old "She could sabotage the vote, make sure nobody won, but the threat of the Mythrans was too real to risk that."
    new "She could sabotage the vote, make sure nobody won, but the threat of the Mythrans was too real to risk that."

    old "Maeiv began slowly, then committed."
    new "Maeiv began slowly, then committed."

    old "I too will pledge my support for Edmond."
    new "I too will pledge my support for Edmond."

    old "Antonio bashed the table."
    new "Antonio bashed the table."

    old "I won't accept serving under this man."
    new "I won't accept serving under this man."

    old "Edmond quickly stood up."
    new "Edmond quickly stood up."

    old "Very well. Leave if you wish."
    new "Very well. Leave if you wish."

    old "Antonio made a motion to leave."
    new "Antonio made a motion to leave."

    old "But remember this."
    new "But remember this."

    old "This Union will be formed with your support or without it. And as you can see, I will be promoted as its leader."
    new "This Union will be formed with your support or without it. And as you can see, I will be promoted as its leader."

    old "Fine! Do whatever you wish, but you will be doing it without me."
    new "Fine! Do whatever you wish, but you will be doing it without me."

    old "Edmond blocked Antonio's exit."
    new "Edmond blocked Antonio's exit."

    old "And my first proposal will be to send a message to the Mythrans. Announcing the formation of our Union."
    new "And my first proposal will be to send a message to the Mythrans. Announcing the formation of our Union."

    old "What do I care? Do as you wish I said!"
    new "What do I care? Do as you wish I said!"

    old "And that letter will be informing the Mythrans that Elarand, Normandi and Rosanna have formed into a single, strong, unified block."
    new "And that letter will be informing the Mythrans that Elarand, Normandi and Rosanna have formed into a single, strong, unified block."

    old "Sarah saw Antonio's face drop."
    new "Sarah saw Antonio's face drop."

    old "Yes. I will let the Mythrans know exactly where the weak point in our continent's defense is."
    new "Yes. I will let the Mythrans know exactly where the weak point in our continent's defense is."

    old "Your decrepit little corner."
    new "Your decrepit little corner."

    old "That is treason!"
    new "That is treason!"

    old "Edmond waved about the room."
    new "Edmond waved about the room."

    old "All the rulers of the other nations on our side of the sea are here."
    new "All the rulers of the other nations on our side of the sea are here."

    old "You wish to file a complaint with any of them?"
    new "You wish to file a complaint with any of them?"

    old "You expect to find any allies here?"
    new "You expect to find any allies here?"

    old "Sarah could see sweat begin to form on Antonio's face."
    new "Sarah could see sweat begin to form on Antonio's face."

    old "A smile appeared on Edmond's face. He knew he had his rival where he wanted him."
    new "A smile appeared on Edmond's face. He knew he had his rival where he wanted him."

    old "I may have spoken with too much haste."
    new "I may have spoken with too much haste."

    old "You must forgive me, good friend. We Medini are...emotional people."
    new "You must forgive me, good friend. We Medini are...emotional people."

    old "Edmond patted the Duke on his shoulders in a condescending way."
    new "Edmond patted the Duke on his shoulders in a condescending way."

    old "Worry not my little fat friend."
    new "Worry not my little fat friend."

    old "I will begin my rule of the Union as a most forgiving Leader."
    new "I will begin my rule of the Union as a most forgiving Leader."

    old "Edmond leaned in closer."
    new "Edmond leaned in closer."

    old "But let us make sure that will be the last of your emotional outbursts, before my kind nature runs out."
    new "But let us make sure that will be the last of your emotional outbursts, before my kind nature runs out."

    old "Antonio gritted his teeth and nodded."
    new "Antonio gritted his teeth and nodded."

    old "Very well, then I will take on the mantle of old."
    new "Very well, then I will take on the mantle of old."

    old "High King of the Union."
    new "High King of the Union."

    old "I vow that I will wield this immense power, conscious of the weight that now rests on my shoulder."
    new "I vow that I will wield this immense power, conscious of the weight that now rests on my shoulder."

    old "Together, each of them raised a cup in celebration of their new High King."
    new "Together, each of them raised a cup in celebration of their new High King."

    old "Support Antonio"
    new "Support Antonio"

    old "I pledge my support to Antonio."
    new "I pledge my support to Antonio."

    old "Thank you, Sarah. There is a girl with a smart head on her shoulders."
    new "Thank you, Sarah. There is a girl with a smart head on her shoulders."

    old "Edmond let out a loud laugh."
    new "Edmond let out a loud laugh."

    old "Please, you must be joking."
    new "Please, you must be joking."

    old "Maeiv joined in."
    new "Maeiv joined in."

    old "Smart? If anything she must have gone insane to propose you of all people."
    new "Smart? If anything she must have gone insane to propose you of all people."

    old "Edmond shook his head."
    new "Edmond shook his head."

    old "I can tolerate a lot, but not this fat ghoul. I will never tolerate it."
    new "I can tolerate a lot, but not this fat ghoul. I will never tolerate it."

    old "I agree. We would be better off with no leader at all than...him."
    new "I agree. We would be better off with no leader at all than...him."

    old "Sarah tried to get another word in, but the room was lost to her and fell back into infighting."
    new "Sarah tried to get another word in, but the room was lost to her and fell back into infighting."

    old "For nearly an hour, they went on and on, exchanging insults and incriminations."
    new "For nearly an hour, they went on and on, exchanging insults and incriminations."

    old "Finally, they settled on the only proposal that any of them could live with."
    new "Finally, they settled on the only proposal that any of them could live with."

    old "There would be no leader at all. A Council would rule instead."
    new "There would be no leader at all. A Council would rule instead."

